output.name: VerdantCedarFund
output.description: VerdantCedarFund is a nonprofit research organization that identifies and funds cost-effective global health and poverty alleviation programs. Since its founding in 2007, it has directed over $2.4 billion in grants and is recognized as one of the world’s largest private funders of development efforts. Known for its rigorous, transparent evidence-based approach and commitment to measuring impact, VerdantCedarFund partners with tens of thousands of donors to drive life-saving interventions in the world’s lowest-income communities.
